AB  - In this paper we evaluate under a squared error loss measure the risk of a two-stage pre-test estimator (2SPE) for the two-sample problem where there is uncertainty concerning both the equality of the location vectors and the scale parameters. The risk performance of the 2SPE is analytically derived and numerically evaluated and compared with that of other traditional estimators that have been proposed for this statistical model.
